DeepTrack data

Junyao Jiang

2025-04-09

This page offers descriptions and download links for all well-processed sequencing data from the DeepTrack paper.

Download link

https://westlakeu-my.sharepoint.com/:f:/g/personal/jiangjunyao_westlake_edu_cn/EufAKGyghTBMlg5e5msQYHIBFQMjWldc4iNGNXF2PB8cnQ?e=eH5eZa

Data descriptions

Experiment 1: Bulk lineage tracing (Figure1)

Bulk lineage tracing.csv: This is bulk lineage tracing data from two E18.5 mouse embryos. Each row represents a single clone, and each column represents a single tissue.

Experiment 2: Single cell lineage tracing (Figure2-3)

single cell lineage tracing.h5ad: This is a well-processed AnnData object encompassing all single-cell lineage tracing data featured in Figures 2-3. The dataset comprises 118,563 cells across four distinct time points (E8.0, E8.5, E9.0, and E9.5) from six mouse embryos. The barcodes column in the obs attribute represents cell-specific lineage barcodes.

Experiment 3: Single cell multiomics lineage tracing (Figure4)

single cell multiomics lineage tracing.h5ad: This is a well-processed AnnData object that encompasses all multiomics single-cell lineage tracing data featured in Figure 4. The dataset contains 60,355 cells with multi-modality from two E9.5 mouse embryos. The barcodes column in the obs attribute represents cell-specific lineage barcodes.

Experiment 4: scRNA-seq for Cdx2-mutant embryos (Figure5)

Cdx2 KO.h5ad: This is a well-processed AnnData object for scRNA-seq data from E10.5 Cdx2-mutant chimeras, including 11,098 Cdx2-mutant cells and 13,901 wild-type cells.
